African Union Peacekeepers in Somalia Start ‘Operation’ Against Insurgents

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-05-12T14:30:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/african-union-peacekeepers-in-somalia-start-operation-against-insurgents.html
The African Union peacekeeping
mission in Somalia started an operation yesterday with local
troops against Islamic insurgents in the Hodan and Hawlwadag
districts, Amisom, as the mission is known, said.  The operation led to the death of a commander of the
insurgents in Hawlwadag, and several fighters, it said in an e-
mailed statement today from Mogadishu, the capital. Two Amisom
soldiers were killed and three injured, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  